INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (1,1,'2015-01-14 22:07:42','2015-01-14 22:07:42','Welcome to WordPress. This is your first post. Edit or delete it, then start blogging!','Hello world!','','publish','open','open','','hello-world','','','2015-01-20 21:51:36','2015-01-20 21:51:36','',0,'/?p=1',0,'post','',1),(5,1,'2015-01-14 22:46:58','2015-01-14 22:46:58','','bg-home','','inherit','open','open','','bg-home','','','2015-01-14 22:46:58','2015-01-14 22:46:58','',0,'/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/bg-home.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(7,1,'2015-01-15 21:34:11','2015-01-15 21:34:11','','Home','','publish','closed','open','','home','','','2015-01-15 21:34:11','2015-01-15 21:34:11','',0,'/?page_id=7',0,'page','',0),(8,1,'2015-01-15 21:34:11','2015-01-15 21:34:11','','Home','','inherit','closed','open','','7-revision-v1','','','2015-01-15 21:34:11','2015-01-15 21:34:11','',7,'/7-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(11,1,'2015-01-16 20:20:18','2015-01-16 20:20:18','I am a paramedic with a local ambulance service. I had my first lumbar lamenectomy in 2003. The neurosurgeon I had then made a very large incision on my back to remove herniated disk material that was compressing a nerve which was causing excruciating right leg pain and numbness. I lost a lot of blood in surgery and it took me 6 months to recover completely from that type of surgery. In July 2007 Dr. Maioriello performed a minimal invasive lumbar lamenectomy for a herniated disk which was causing severe pain and numbness in my left leg. This surgery was also done to remove herniated disk material that was compressing a nerve that was causing leg pain and numbness. Because of the minimal invasive technique used by Dr. Maioriello there was much less pain and I was able to heal much faster compared to the traditional surgery. My new incision is tiny compared to the old incision. I was walking on the treadmill 1 day post op and by one week post op I was walking miles and swimming pain free. I credit Dr. Maioriello for being able to go back to work 3 weeks after surgery with no restrictions. Thank you Dr. Maioriello.','Chad F.','','publish','closed','closed','','chad-f','','','2015-01-20 22:09:52','2015-01-20 22:09:52','',0,'/?post_type=testimonials&#038;p=11',0,'testimonials','',0),(12,1,'2015-01-16 20:34:17','2015-01-16 20:34:17','My new incision is tiny compared to the other, there was minimal blood loss, and I was walking on my treadmill the next day. ','Dorothy H.','','publish','closed','closed','','dorothy-h','','','2015-01-16 20:43:57','2015-01-16 20:43:57','',0,'/?post_type=quotes&#038;p=12',0,'quotes','',0),(13,1,'2015-01-16 20:45:21','2015-01-16 20:45:21','I am a paramedic with a local ambulance service. I had my first lumbar lamenectomy in 2003. The neurosurgeon I had then made a very large incision on my back to remove herniated disk material that was compressing a nerve which was causing excruciating right leg pain and numbness. I lost a lot of blood in surgery and it took me 6 months to recover completely from that type of surgery. In July 2007 Dr. Maioriello performed a minimal invasive lumbar lamenectomy for a herniated disk which was causing severe pain and numbness in my left leg. This surgery was also done to remove herniated disk material that was compressing a nerve that was causing leg pain and numbness. Because of the minimal invasive technique used by Dr. Maioriello there was much less pain and I was able to heal much faster compared to the traditional surgery. My new incision is tiny compared to the old incision. I was walking on the treadmill 1 day post op and by one week post op I was walking miles and swimming pain free. I credit Dr. Maioriello for being able to go back to work 3 weeks after surgery with no restrictions. Thank you Dr. Maioriello.','Chad F.','','inherit','closed','open','','11-autosave-v1','','','2015-01-16 20:45:21','2015-01-16 20:45:21','',11,'/11-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(14,1,'2015-01-16 20:46:30','2015-01-16 20:46:30','Fifteen months ago I was not sure I would walk again without the aid of a cane, walker, or other assistive device. I had such pain in my right leg, that I was able to move only with baby steps and a cane. I had a history of lower back pain since I was 18. I had doctored with my Family Physician in Clinton for years. I am now 62 years old. My Family Physician referred me to Iowa City several years ago and they found nothing to treat. He referred me to the Pain Clinic in the Quad Cities. After several years of epidural shots in my back, my problem continued, with mild short term relief. My Family Physician continued to follow my case, and finally referred me to the Neurology Team at Genesis.\r\n\r\nAfter reviewing X-Rays, MRI\'s and CAT Scans, Dr. Maioriello, determined that I was a candidate for a fusion of vertebrate 4 & 5. This was done in July, 2006. The surgery was not an easy one to recover from. It took a several months of Physical Therapy to regain my muscle strength, but the entire process was well worth it. I can now move about without the aid of a cane. I take regular steps, walk on the treadmill 40 minutes a day, maintain several gardens and a pond, and am golfing 2-3 times per week. I am grateful to Dr. Maioriello and the Surgical Team and the Physical Therapy Team who made these positive results for me.','Jack P.','','publish','closed','closed','','jack-pringle','','','2015-02-13 00:59:43','2015-02-13 00:59:43','',0,'/?post_type=testimonials&#038;p=14',0,'testimonials','',0),(15,1,'2015-01-16 20:48:19','2015-01-16 20:48:19','Dr. Maioriello, to all who read.\r\n\r\nMy many thanks to Dr. Maioriello for his outstanding skill, compassionate manner and professionalism.\r\n\r\nI came to Dr. Maioriello as a young very active 51-year-old male that (had) multiple issues, the most prominent (I thought) my lower-back discomfort.\r\n\r\nDuring my initial consultation, Dr. Maioriello picked-up on my hyper-reflexivity, noting that it is a sign of concern. A spinal MRI revealed two herniated disks in my neck, what a surprise, if an accident occurred I could be paralyzed!\r\n\r\nDr. Maioriello is genuinely concerned that his patients have the information to make proper decisions, their wellness and peace of mind.\r\n\r\nWhen I made the decision to move forward with the procedure I felt part of a team, even just prior to surgery. In need of mention is Dr. Maioriello’s wife Bella who manages the business and the staff, good folks.\r\n\r\nWhen you select a surgeon you hope that the person has what it takes, let me tell you, my second walk just hours after surgery, I was halfway around the building and realized I had no back pain, I cried, literally, I was so happy. I can only tell you.','Greg L.','','publish','closed','closed','','greg-leclaire-ia','','','2015-04-17 21:16:24','2015-04-17 21:16:24','',0,'/?post_type=testimonials&#038;p=15',0,'testimonials','',0),(16,1,'2015-01-19 21:54:25','2015-01-19 21:54:25','We succeed when we meet and exceed the expectations of our patients. We have a passion for excellence and endeavor to set and deliver the highest standards of service, value, integrity, and availability. We feel a sense of responsibility to be leaders in the field of neurosurgery and utilize cutting edge techniques and technologies to improve outcomes.\r\n\r\nAt Minimally Invasive Brain and Spine, we understand the distress that patients feel when they need a neurosurgeon. Whether they are suffering from chronic neck or back pain, at risk of dying from a brain tumor or in critical condition from a traumatic brain injury or stroke. We strive to not only handle these most difficult situations, but also take care of the patient and their families in a compassionate manner. We are emotionally invested with our patient’s outcome and will work tirelessly to see it through.','Philosophy','','publish','closed','open','','philosophy','','','2015-01-19 22:01:09','2015-01-19 22:01:09','',0,'/?page_id=16',0,'page','',0),(17,1,'2015-01-19 21:54:25